\section{Discussion}
\subsection{Reduced chi-squared tests}
The underlying assumption for the weighted mean to be a valid parameter estimate is that individual measurements of that parameter are normally distributed around the same mean value with variances $\sigma_i^2$, and there are no systematic errors. The reduced chi-squared can be used to test, in part, this hypothesis:
